SIMPLE: repellent
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Repellent
<hw>Re*pel"lent</hw> <pr>(-l<it>e</it>nt)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>repellens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. ]</ety> <def>Driving
back; able or tending to repel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Repellent</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Repellent
<hw>Re*pel"lent</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>That which
repels.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A remedy to repel from a tumefied
part the fluids which render it tumid.</def>
<rj><au>Dunglison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A kind of waterproof cloth.</def>
<rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Repeller</ent>⟦br⟧
